(455, 1, '2016-08-02 14:13:11', '2016-08-02 14:13:11', '<p>Set within the Borough of Richmond upon Thames, Brewery Wharf is a new development of 82 luxury apartments and 28 gated houses, 2 restaurants, public piazza and a cultural venue. Best known for world famous Twickenham Stadium, this area is much sought after due to its excellent schools, beautiful riverside walks, historical landmarks, museums and green open spaces.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n•     Close to Kingston &amp; Richmond<br />\r\n•     Excellent school catchment area<br />\r\n•     0.5 miles to the River Thames<br />\r\n•     Opposite Twickenham Train Station\r\n</p>\r\n \r\n<p>The regeneration of the former Royal Mail Sorting Office in Twickenham will produce a vibrant community with 110 residential homes, community building and public piazza.  But this is not the only thing that is planned for Twickenham.  It is part of a wider regeneration plan which will see millions of pounds ploughed into the area over the next 14 years.  Environmental improvements are being undertaken all over the borough as well as plans having been approved for the regeneration of Twickenham Station, bringing about improvement to make the station fit for the 21st century</p>', 'Brewery Wharf', 'Twickenham TW1 1AA', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '94-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-02 14:13:11', '2016-08-02 14:13:11', '', 94, 'http://brandstallion.com/eylsianglobal/2016/08/02/94-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
